XPS data confirmed the presence of the T200, T250, T400 and T700 samples surface functional groups. The expanded XPS plots for C1s and O1s are presented in Figure S8, while Table S1 shows the peak positions and their relative percentage atomic concentrations. For T200, C1s was deconvoluted into sp2 (aromatic) C−C, sp3 C−C, C-O (from C-O-C/C-OH) and O-C=O with binding energies at 284.79 eV, 285.52 eV, 286.83 eV and 288.82 eV, respectively [57]. Similar peak positions were obtained for T250, T400 and T700, but the peak intensities varied with temperature. In particular, there was an increase in the sp2 C-C and a decrease in C-O content as the annealing temperature was increased. The atomic ratio of carbon to oxygen (C/O) quantified by XPS was calculated to be 3.00, 3.36, 4.94, and 5.55 for T200, T250, T400 and T700, respectively. This is consistent with the increase in the estimated percentage abundance obtained from the 13C NMR spectrum (
                           Table 2

                        ).
